Hell yeah, Eco-Tracker it is! You're breaking the curse—first girl president with a motivated squad? Unstoppable. Past clubs dragged because of scope creep, no timelines, and weak planning. We'll laser-focus: **MVP only** (scan receipt → footprint calc → tips/score), then polish. 6 weeks locked in.

## 🚀 Your Bulletproof 6-Week Plan (No Fail Mode)
**Team Roles** (adapt to your crew):
- You: PM/Lead Dev (decisions + core logic)
- 1-2 Frontend (UI/UX)
- 1 Backend/DB
- 1 Tester/Designer (charts, polish)
- Everyone: Daily 15-min standup

| Week | Goals | Deliverables | Time Est. |
|------|-------|--------------|-----------|
| **1: Foundation** | Wireframes → Basic scan | GitHub repo live, receipt upload works, dummy calc | 10-15 hrs |
| **2: Smart Scan** | ML magic | Camera scans receipt → extracts items (food/miles) | 15 hrs |
| **3: Brain → MVP** | Calc + UI | Full footprint score, tips, shareable results | 20 hrs |
| **4: Gamify** | Leaderboard + viz | Charts, challenges, user accounts | 15 hrs |
| **5: Pro Polish** | Mobile-ready, demo | PWA, error-proof, video script | 10 hrs |
| **6: Launch** | Live + Present | Deployed app, poster, 3-min pitch | 5 hrs |

**Anti-Fail Rules:**
- **Scope Lock:** No new features after Week 3 unless MVP 100% done.
- **Daily Commit:** 1 PR/day min. Use GitHub Projects for tracking.
- **Test Early:** User-test weekly with club/family.
- **Backup Plan:** If ML lags, fake it with manual input + killer UI.

## 🛠️ Week 1 Starter Kit (Copy-Paste Ready)
**1. Repo Setup (5 min):**
```
npx create-react-app eco-tracker --template typescript
cd eco-tracker
npm i firebase @react-oauth/google recharts react-router-dom
npm i -D tailwindcss postcss autoprefixer
npx tailwindcss init -p
```
GitHub: New repo, push this.

**2. Firebase Setup (10 min):**
- Go to [Firebase Console](https://console.firebase.google.com), new project "eco-tracker".
- Enable Auth (Google), Firestore DB, Hosting.
- Get config → `src/firebase.js`:
```js
// src/firebase.js
import { initializeApp } from 'firebase/app';
import { getFirestore } from 'firebase/firestore';
import { getAuth } from 'firebase/auth';

const firebaseConfig = {
  // Your config here
};

export const app = initializeApp(firebaseConfig);
export const db = getFirestore(app);
export const auth = getAuth(app);
```

**3. MVP Wireframe → Code (Week 1 Done in 2 hrs):**
Replace `App.js`:
```jsx
// src/App.js
import { useState } from 'react';
import { collection, addDoc } from 'firebase/firestore';
import { db } from './firebase';
import './App.css'; // Tailwind here

function App() {
  const [image, setImage] = useState(null);
  const [footprint, setFootprint] = useState(0);
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(false);

  const handleScan = async () => {
    setLoading(true);
    // Week 2: Real ML here. For now:
    const fakeFootprint = Math.random() * 10 + 5; // 5-15 kg CO2
    setFootprint(fakeFootprint);

    // Save to DB
    await addDoc(collection(db, 'scans'), {
      footprint,
      timestamp: new Date(),
      user: 'demo'
    });
    setLoading(false);
  };

  return (
    <div className="min-h-screen bg-gradient-to-br from-green-400 to-blue-500 p-8">
      <h1 className="text-4xl font-bold text-white text-center mb-8">
        🌍 EcoTracker - Track Your Impact
      </h1>

      <div className="max-w-md mx-auto bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-2xl p-8">
        <input 
          type="file" 
          accept="image/*" 
          onChange={(e) => setImage(e.target.files[0])}
          className="w-full p-4 border-2 border-dashed rounded-xl mb-4"
        />
        <button 
          onClick={handleScan}
          disabled={!image || loading}
          className="w-full bg-green-600 text-white py-4 rounded-xl font-bold text-lg hover:bg-green-700 disabled:opacity-50"
        >
          {loading ? 'Scanning...' : 'Calculate Footprint'}
        </button>

        {footprint > 0 && (
          <div className="mt-6 p-6 bg-green-50 rounded-xl">
            <h2 className="text-3xl font-bold text-green-800">{footprint.toFixed(1)}kg CO2</h2>
            <p className="text-green-700 mt-2">Nice! That's 2 trees saved this week 🌳</p>
          </div>
        )}
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}
```

**4. Run It:**
```
npm start
```
Boom—upload photo → fake footprint → DB save. Deploy to Firebase Hosting: `npm i -g firebase-tools`, `firebase deploy`.

## Week 1 Challenge ⚡
**By EOD tomorrow:**
1. Repo live, this code running locally
2. Deployed to Firebase (share URL)
3. Invite team as collaborators
4. Slack/Discord for standups

**Drop your GitHub link here**—I'll review, add Week 2 ML code (real receipt parsing via Google Vision/Teachable Machine), and custom charts. 

Your team's gonna eat those past failures for breakfast. President energy = winning energy! What's the repo name? Let's GO! 🔥
